This paper deals with analyzing HTTPS traffic and inferring HTTP semantics without decryption, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential uses of traffic analysis for application troubleshooting and malware detection, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic approach to solving classification problems, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
